OL,3,CDES drug scandal: Health secretary
OL,4,Cadmits 'state got this wrong'
OL,6,FThe regulator then admitted that
OL,7,Finformation was incorrect, and the
OL,8,Fdrug was not stopped for use in
OL,9,Fpregnancy until the 1980s, more than a
OL,10,Fdecade after cancer risks were known.
OL,12,FThe health secretary's acknowledgement
OL,13,Fof the harm this week is a significant
OL,14,Fdevelopment, but he has been careful
OL,15,Fwith his wording to not accept
OL,16,Fliability.
OL,18,FFor the victims of DES who have waited
OL,19,Fso long for their voices to be heard,
OL,20,Fthey are now a step closer to justice,
OL,21,Fbut they still have a long fight to go.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/14
